@evaluate_source
title: Evaluate the source of resources
tags: source_use_aspects

Me: Evaluate the source of resources.

Facilyn: Consider where your energy or money comes from. Is it from unlimited sources (like solar) or limited ones (like fossil fuels)? Is it from benign sources or potentially damaging ones?

- #source_options

@evaluate_use
title: Evaluate the use of resources
tags: source_use_aspects

Me: Evaluate the use of resources.

Facilyn: Consider how you're using energy or money. Is it for infrastructure (lasting benefits), cyclical needs (renewable cycles), consumptive purposes (one-time use), or potentially addictive patterns?

- #use_options

@need_clarification_em
title: I need clarification on this check
tags: source_use_aspects

Me: I need clarification on this check.

Facilyn: Think about sustainability in both directions. Good sources are renewable, benign, and don't deplete natural or social capital. Good uses create lasting value, support natural cycles, or meet genuine needs rather than creating dependencies.

Facilyn: For money, internal sources (from your own productivity) are generally more sustainable than external debt. For energy, renewable sources are preferable to finite ones.

A solar-powered robot tends the teahouse garden, its panels gleaming in the afternoon sun while it waters plants with collected rainwater - a perfect example of appropriate source and use alignment.

